{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reduce VAT to 5% on public EV charging",
        "additional_details": "Many households who have or want an Electric Vehicle (EV) are left with no option but to use public charging as their household has no way to install a home charger, leaving them with the inflated prices of public charging.\r\n \r\nHome energy is set at a VAT rate of only 5% and feel it is only fair that public charging networks are set at the same rate.\r\n",
        "background": "Public EV charging carries a VAT rate of 20%. The UK Government are trying to reach net zero and I believe one way to help achieve this would be to reduce the VAT to 5% on public EV charging.",
